        <!-- 3. Policy & Legislation -->
        <section id="policy" class="py-20 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-secondary mb-4 text-center">
                    Driving Change: Policy Solutions
                </h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-center text-gray-600 mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                    We champion common-sense, evidence-based legislative measures that stop repeat offenders and save thousands of lives annually.
                </p>

                <div class="space-y-12">
                    <!-- Policy 1: Ignition Interlocks -->
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
                        <i data-lucide="car" class="w-12 h-12 text-accent mr-6 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"></i>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">All-Offender Ignition Interlocks</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">These devices, which prevent a vehicle from starting if the driver has been drinking, are the most effective tool for preventing recidivism. We advocate for mandatory interlocks for *all* convicted drunk drivers, including first-time offenders.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Policy 2: BAC Limits -->
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
                        <i data-lucide="gauge" class="w-12 h-12 text-accent mr-6 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"></i>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Lowering the Legal BAC Limit</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">We push for lowering the legal Blood Alcohol Concentration (BAC) limit to $0.05 \text{ g/dL}$. Impairment begins long before $0.08\%$. Adopting a lower limit addresses impairment earlier, aligning the law with the science of safe driving.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <!-- Policy 3: Repeat Offender Laws -->
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-start bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
                        <i data-lucide="lock" class="w-12 h-12 text-accent mr-6 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"></i>
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Mandatory Sentencing for Repeat Offenders</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">Chronic drunk drivers pose an extreme risk. We advocate for mandatory, enhanced penalties, including longer sentences and intensified supervision, to ensure public safety and accountability.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- CTA: Contact Legislator -->
                <div class="mt-12 text-center">
                    <a href="#" class="bg-primary hover:bg-secondary text-white font-bold py-4 px-10 rounded-full text-lg shadow-lg transition duration-300 transform hover:scale-105 inline-flex items-center">
                        <i data-lucide="send" class="w-5 h-5 mr-3"></i> Contact Your Legislator
                    </a>
                    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">Use our tool to quickly find and contact your local representative about pending DUI laws.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. Facts, Data, & Prevention -->
        <section id="data" class="py-20 bg-gray-100">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
                <h2 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-primary mb-4 text-center">
                    Facts, Data, & Prevention
                </h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-center text-gray-600 mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                    Knowledge is power. Understand the science of impairment and plan ahead for a safe ride home.
                </p>

                <!-- Impairment Explained -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-xl mb-12">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b pb-2">Impairment Explained</h3>
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-red-50 rounded-lg">
                            <p class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-red-600">0.02% BAC</p>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold">Loss of judgment, decline in visual function.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 bg-orange-50 rounded-lg">
                            <p class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-orange-600">0.05% BAC</p>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold">Reduced coordination, difficulty steering, less inhibited.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4 bg-red-100 rounded-lg">
                            <p class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-red-700">0.08% BAC (Legal Limit)</p>
                            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 font-semibold">Major loss of muscle control, slowed reaction time, difficulty processing information.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="mt-6 text-sm italic text-gray-500 text-center">Impairment begins with the first drink. Never take chances.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Prevention Checklist -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-xl">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 border-b pb-2">Prevention Checklist: Get Home Safe</h3>
                    <ul class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 text-lg">
                        <li class="flex items-center"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></i> **Designated Drivers:** Secure a sober driver BEFORE you go out.</li>
                        <li class="flex items-center"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></i> **Ride-Share/Taxi:** Download and use apps like Uber or Lyft, or keep local taxi numbers ready.</li>
                        <li class="flex items-center"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></i> **Public Transit:** Plan your bus or train route and schedule in advance.</li>
                        <li class="flex items-center"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-6 h-6 text-primary mr-3 flex-shrink-0"></i> **Host Responsibility:** If hosting, offer non-alcoholic options and ensure every guest has a safe way home.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

